metadata.name: The String #330
metadata.description:
|| Anniversary project for FX(hash) 1st birthday ||

Each virtual object consists of 365 lights.
Each light represents one day of the year.

We go through every single day, thinking it's all crucial. Yet, from a perspective, it all gets compressed into a single thread. Some of the events are brighter and more memorable. Others just blend or fade away.

I welcomed November 2021 with huge excitement and celebration. The joyful beginning of the month was followed by weeks of misery, anxiety, denial, and acceptance. It was a hard time, but in the long run, it was liberating and started a process of change. Change that happens dynamically to this day.

I couldn't join you last year, but I'm celebrating with you today!



In memory of my Dad.



Donations:
40% – Savepakistan - Flood Relief Fundraiser
10% – Three.js

metadata.name: HOWL.camera #29
metadata.description:
Created with the permission and endorsement of Allen Ginsberg's estate, enabled by theVERSEverse, this work channels Ginsberg's iconic poem HOWL through a dynamic ASCII lens.

Written by Ross Goodwin using 54 of Ginsberg's original photographs and a Markov language model of HOWL in vanilla JS. Each edition shifts from the minter's chosen photograph after 10 seconds into pure ASCII noise, eventually devolving into chaotic Markov fragments.

60% of mint and royalty proceeds will be donated to benefit victims of the recent Los Angeles fires.

https://howl.camera

metadata.name: Shift #102
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm honing the power of vertical displacement.

How simple may a generative algorithm be while simultaneously staying diverse enough for each art piece to be truly unique? Shift is the result of an exploration into this space, basing its existence on two principles — dissection and vertical shifting. Each variable in this art engine has been meticulously weighted, giving rise to high diversity and the possibility of epic combinations. 

Shift is a series of 888 unique pieces.

############

Display resolution is 1000x1400. Press ’s’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x8400 hi-res image. This may take a while to generate depending on your hardware.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022

metadata.name: night fall moon #50
metadata.description:
it all starts with circles and squares. (but that’s hidden behind flashing lights.)

it gets pulled over and down and then over piece by piece, haphazardly so, and then possibly pulled down again. (but not always.)

it can take a while to process. (like a lot of things.)

it can feel like falling. (possibly, spinning.)

seeing it all can take focus. (but sometimes an impression is all you need.)

you can process it more if you like. (but eventually you’ll be left with nothing.)

[ in “live view” you can press: ]

metadata.name: Mina #96
metadata.description:
A generative series of a-symmetric compositions.

Mina is a search for new textures created by combining 3 colors with 3 different mathematical equations.

Observe how Mina blends and creates its textures in time.

Probabilities;

- 18 color palettes.

- 2 background colors.

- 4 line placements.

- 14 different compositions, most of them have variations.


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, December 2021
@distcollective

metadata.name: Zee  #4
metadata.description:
As wild as it is, for me the sea has something soothing. The rushing of the waves, the strong wind in your face, the salty air, the screeching of seagulls, freezing rain. At the coast it is easy to forget everything and be in the moment. The view is expansive and no matter how ominous the clouds, somewhere the sun breaks through. 

At the same time, the raging sea can be life-threatening. Many have lost their lives at sea or by the sea, some by flooding, some in the battle for peace, others in search of a better life. 

The sea, with its many faces and stories, is beautiful, terrifying and everything in between. 

#Features
Are there birds, and if so, how many?
Is it raining?
How cloudy is it?
How rough is the sea?

Generative art coded with p5js.
